Distribution of grants by funder, type of grant and average grant duration As shown in Table 1 , a total of 69,420 grants were provided by the 10 funding organisations in 2016. The United States of America's NIH funded the greatest number of grants (52,928; 76%) and had the longest average grant duration (6 years and 10 months). Out of the total number of grants, 70.4% were for research (48, 879), followed by training (13,008; 18.7%) and meetings (2907; 4.2%) (Fig. 1 ). 